Katja and Claudia, both recovered from eating disorders, opened Germany's first restaurant for anorexics and bulimics.
Claudia, wearing a chef's hat, cooks for those struggling like her.
The establishment provides a safe space for those transitioning to normal life.
Meanwhile, in Italy, TV ads targeting children with food products are linked to eating disorders.
Researchers are exploring the role of leptin in restoring menstruation in female athletes.
Treatment for binge-eating disorder shows promise, but insurance coverage remains a challenge.
Middle-aged women also face challenges with eating disorders, highlighting the need for more research and support.
